{
  "doc_id": "1540",
  "text": "Immunoblotting was performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . ImmunoStar AP (Bio-Rad) was used as a substrate for chemiluminescence, and images were acquired using Luminoimage analyzer LAS 4000 (Fujifilm). Immunofluorescence microscopy was performed essentially as described previously . Images were acquired using a Radiance 2000 confocal microscope (Bio-Rad). Changes in mitochondrial morphology were calculated (as means ± s.d.) using data from at least three independent experiments. In each experiment, 100-200 individual cells were counted. Antibodies used for immunoblotting and immunofluorescence microscopy were as follows: rabbit polyclonal antibodies: anti-Tim17 [CITATION_2] , anti-Sec61 (Upstate), anti-H450 [CITATION_3] , anti-Tom40 [CITATION_4] ; mouse monoclonal antibodies: anti-HA (16B12) (Covance).",
